FBIS3-35106 "drnes034_n_94005" FBIS-NES-94-034 Document Type:Daily Report 18 Feb 1994 LEBANON Tension in South Amid `Enemy' Reinforcements House Hit by Israeli Fire NC1702185894 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1715 GMT 17 Feb 94 NC1702185894 Beirut Voice of Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Excerpts] There is caution and tension in the south. While Israel takes a grave view of the firing of Katyusha rockets at the Galilee, as Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres says, Hizballah, through [Deputy Secretary General] Na'im Qasim, stresses that resistance against Israel will continue. President Ilyas al-Hirawi, U.S. Ambassador to Lebanon Mark Hambley, and Army Commander General Emil Lahhud today assessed developments in the south. [passage omitted] Events in the south and the region were reviewed in a meeting between Syrian President Hafiz al-Asad and Lebanese Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri in Damascus at noon today. [passage omitted] Israel renewed its machine-gun fire against Kafr Rumman this afternoon. Citizen Muhammad Najm's house was hit and caught fire. Civil defense brigades in al-Nabatiyah put out the fire. The Israeli forces kept the Zummarayya crossing closed for a second day but opened the al-Hamra' crossing. [passage omitted]
